322isc_result_t
323named_config_parsedefaults(cfg_parser_t *parser, cfg_obj_t **conf) {
324 isc_buffer_t b;
325
326 isc_buffer_init(&b, defaultconf, sizeof(defaultconf) - 1);
327 isc_buffer_add(&b, sizeof(defaultconf) - 1);
328 return (cfg_parse_buffer(parser, &b, __FILE__, 0,
329 &cfg_type_namedconf,
330 CFG_PCTX_NODEPRECATED, conf));
331}
332
333isc_result_t
334named_config_get(cfg_obj_t const * const *maps, const char *name,
335 const cfg_obj_t **obj)
336{
337 int i;
338
339 for (i = 0;; i++) {
340 if (maps[i] == NULL)
341 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
342 if (cfg_map_get(maps[i], name, obj) == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
343 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
344 }
345}
346
347isc_result_t
348named_checknames_get(const cfg_obj_t **maps, const char *which,
349 const cfg_obj_t **obj)
350{
351 const cfg_listelt_t *element;
352 const cfg_obj_t *checknames;
353 const cfg_obj_t *type;
354 const cfg_obj_t *value;
355 int i;
356
357 for (i = 0;; i++) {
358 if (maps[i] == NULL)
359 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
360 checknames = NULL;
361 if (cfg_map_get(maps[i], "check-names",
362 &checknames) == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
363 /*
364 * Zone map entry is not a list.
365 */
366 if (checknames != NULL && !cfg_obj_islist(checknames)) {
367 *obj = checknames;
368 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
369 }
370 for (element = cfg_list_first(checknames);
371 element != NULL;
372 element = cfg_list_next(element)) {
373 value = cfg_listelt_value(element);
374 type = cfg_tuple_get(value, "type");
375 if (strcasecmp(cfg_obj_asstring(type),
376 which) == 0) {
377 *obj = cfg_tuple_get(value, "mode");
378 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
379 }
380 }
381
382 }
383 }
384}
385
386int
387named_config_listcount(const cfg_obj_t *list) {
388 const cfg_listelt_t *e;
389 int i = 0;
390
391 for (e = cfg_list_first(list); e != NULL; e = cfg_list_next(e))
392 i++;
393
394 return (i);
395}

397isc_result_t
398named_config_getclass(const cfg_obj_t *classobj, dns_rdataclass_t defclass,
399 dns_rdataclass_t *classp)
400{
401 isc_textregion_t r;
402 isc_result_t result;
403
404 if (!cfg_obj_isstring(classobj)) {
405 *classp = defclass;
406 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
407 }
408 DE_CONST(cfg_obj_asstring(classobj), r.base);
409 r.length = strlen(r.base);
410 result = dns_rdataclass_fromtext(classp, &r);
411 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
412 cfg_obj_log(classobj, named_g_lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
413 "unknown class '%s'", r.base);
414 return (result);
415}
416
417isc_result_t
418named_config_gettype(const cfg_obj_t *typeobj, dns_rdatatype_t deftype,
419 dns_rdatatype_t *typep)
420{
421 isc_textregion_t r;
422 isc_result_t result;
423
424 if (!cfg_obj_isstring(typeobj)) {
425 *typep = deftype;
426 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
427 }
428 DE_CONST(cfg_obj_asstring(typeobj), r.base);
429 r.length = strlen(r.base);
430 result = dns_rdatatype_fromtext(typep, &r);
431 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
432 cfg_obj_log(typeobj, named_g_lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
433 "unknown type '%s'", r.base);
434 return (result);
435}

437dns_zonetype_t
438named_config_getzonetype(const cfg_obj_t *zonetypeobj) {
439 dns_zonetype_t ztype = dns_zone_none;
440 const char *str;
441
442 str = cfg_obj_asstring(zonetypeobj);
443 if (strcasecmp(str, "primary") == 0 ||
444 strcasecmp(str, "master") == 0)
445 {
446 ztype = dns_zone_master;
447 } else if (strcasecmp(str, "secondary") == 0 ||
448 strcasecmp(str, "slave") == 0)
449 {
450 ztype = dns_zone_slave;
451 } else if (strcasecmp(str, "mirror") == 0) {
452 ztype = dns_zone_mirror;
453 } else if (strcasecmp(str, "stub") == 0) {
454 ztype = dns_zone_stub;
455 } else if (strcasecmp(str, "static-stub") == 0) {
456 ztype = dns_zone_staticstub;
457 } else if (strcasecmp(str, "redirect") == 0) {
458 ztype = dns_zone_redirect;
459 } else {
460 INSIST(0);
461 ISC_UNREACHABLE();
462 }
463 return (ztype);
464}

466isc_result_t
467named_config_getiplist(const cfg_obj_t *config, const cfg_obj_t *list,
468 in_port_t defport, isc_mem_t *mctx,
469 isc_sockaddr_t **addrsp, isc_dscp_t **dscpsp,
470 uint32_t *countp)
471{
472 int count, i = 0;
473 const cfg_obj_t *addrlist;
474 const cfg_obj_t *portobj, *dscpobj;
475 const cfg_listelt_t *element;
476 isc_sockaddr_t *addrs;
477 in_port_t port;
478 isc_dscp_t dscp = -1, *dscps = NULL;
479 isc_result_t result;
480
481 INSIST(addrsp != NULL && *addrsp == NULL);
482 INSIST(dscpsp == NULL || *dscpsp == NULL);
483 INSIST(countp != NULL);
484
485 addrlist = cfg_tuple_get(list, "addresses");
486 count = named_config_listcount(addrlist);
487
488 portobj = cfg_tuple_get(list, "port");
489 if (cfg_obj_isuint32(portobj)) {
490 uint32_t val = cfg_obj_asuint32(portobj);
491 if (val > UINT16_MAX) {
492 cfg_obj_log(portobj, named_g_lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
493 "port '%u' out of range", val);
494 return (ISC_R_RANGE);
495 }
496 port = (in_port_t) val;
497 } else if (defport != 0)
498 port = defport;
499 else {
500 result = named_config_getport(config, &port);
501 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
502 return (result);
503 }
504
505 if (dscpsp != NULL) {
506 dscpobj = cfg_tuple_get(list, "dscp");
507 if (dscpobj != NULL && cfg_obj_isuint32(dscpobj)) {
508 if (cfg_obj_asuint32(dscpobj) > 63) {
509 cfg_obj_log(dscpobj, named_g_lctx,
510 ISC_LOG_ERROR,
511 "dscp value '%u' is out of range",
512 cfg_obj_asuint32(dscpobj));
513 return (ISC_R_RANGE);
514 }
515 dscp = (isc_dscp_t)cfg_obj_asuint32(dscpobj);
516 }
517
518 dscps = isc_mem_get(mctx, count * sizeof(isc_dscp_t));
519 if (dscps == NULL)
520 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
521 }
522
523 addrs = isc_mem_get(mctx, count * sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t));
524 if (addrs == NULL) {
525 if (dscps != NULL)
526 isc_mem_put(mctx, dscps, count * sizeof(isc_dscp_t));
527 return (ISC_R_NOMEMORY);
528 }
529
530 for (element = cfg_list_first(addrlist);
531 element != NULL;
532 element = cfg_list_next(element), i++)
533 {
534 const cfg_obj_t *addr;
535 INSIST(i < count);
536 addr = cfg_listelt_value(element);
537 addrs[i] = *cfg_obj_assockaddr(addr);
538 if (dscpsp != NULL) {
539 isc_dscp_t innerdscp;
540 innerdscp = cfg_obj_getdscp(addr);
541 if (innerdscp == -1)
542 innerdscp = dscp;
543 dscps[i] = innerdscp;
544 }
545 if (isc_sockaddr_getport(&addrs[i]) == 0)
546 isc_sockaddr_setport(&addrs[i], port);
547 }
548 INSIST(i == count);
549
550 *addrsp = addrs;
551 *countp = count;
552
553 if (dscpsp != NULL)
554 *dscpsp = dscps;
555
556 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
557}
558
559void
560named_config_putiplist(isc_mem_t *mctx, isc_sockaddr_t **addrsp,
561 isc_dscp_t **dscpsp, uint32_t count)
562{
563 INSIST(addrsp != NULL && *addrsp != NULL);
564 INSIST(dscpsp == NULL || *dscpsp != NULL);
565
566 isc_mem_put(mctx, *addrsp, count * sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t));
567 *addrsp = NULL;
568
569 if (dscpsp != NULL) {
570 isc_mem_put(mctx, *dscpsp, count * sizeof(isc_dscp_t));
571 *dscpsp = NULL;
572 }
573}
574
575isc_result_t
576named_config_getmastersdef(const cfg_obj_t *cctx, const char *name,
577 const cfg_obj_t **ret)
578{
579 isc_result_t result;
580 const cfg_obj_t *masters = NULL;
581 const cfg_listelt_t *elt;
582
583 result = cfg_map_get(cctx, "masters", &masters);
584 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
585 return (result);
586 for (elt = cfg_list_first(masters);
587 elt != NULL;
588 elt = cfg_list_next(elt)) {
589 const cfg_obj_t *list;
590 const char *listname;
591
592 list = cfg_listelt_value(elt);
593 listname = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_tuple_get(list, "name"));
594
595 if (strcasecmp(listname, name) == 0) {
596 *ret = list;
597 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
598 }
599 }
600 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
601}

603isc_result_t
604named_config_getipandkeylist(const cfg_obj_t *config, const cfg_obj_t *list,
605 isc_mem_t *mctx, dns_ipkeylist_t *ipkl)
606{
607 uint32_t addrcount = 0, dscpcount = 0, keycount = 0, i = 0;
608 uint32_t listcount = 0, l = 0, j;
609 uint32_t stackcount = 0, pushed = 0;
610 isc_result_t result;
611 const cfg_listelt_t *element;
612 const cfg_obj_t *addrlist;
613 const cfg_obj_t *portobj;
614 const cfg_obj_t *dscpobj;
615 in_port_t port;
616 isc_dscp_t dscp = -1;
617 dns_fixedname_t fname;
618 isc_sockaddr_t *addrs = NULL;
619 isc_dscp_t *dscps = NULL;
620 dns_name_t **keys = NULL;
621 struct { const char *name; } *lists = NULL;
622 struct {
623 const cfg_listelt_t *element;
624 in_port_t port;
625 isc_dscp_t dscp;
626 } *stack = NULL;
627
628 REQUIRE(ipkl != NULL);
629 REQUIRE(ipkl->count == 0);
630 REQUIRE(ipkl->addrs == NULL);
631 REQUIRE(ipkl->keys == NULL);
632 REQUIRE(ipkl->dscps == NULL);
633 REQUIRE(ipkl->labels == NULL);
634 REQUIRE(ipkl->allocated == 0);
635
636 /*
637 * Get system defaults.
638 */
639 result = named_config_getport(config, &port);
640 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
641 goto cleanup;
642
643 result = named_config_getdscp(config, &dscp);
644 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
645 goto cleanup;
646
647 newlist:
648 addrlist = cfg_tuple_get(list, "addresses");
649 portobj = cfg_tuple_get(list, "port");
650 dscpobj = cfg_tuple_get(list, "dscp");
651
652 if (cfg_obj_isuint32(portobj)) {
653 uint32_t val = cfg_obj_asuint32(portobj);
654 if (val > UINT16_MAX) {
655 cfg_obj_log(portobj, named_g_lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
656 "port '%u' out of range", val);
657 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
658 goto cleanup;
659 }
660 port = (in_port_t) val;
661 }
662
663 if (dscpobj != NULL && cfg_obj_isuint32(dscpobj)) {
664 if (cfg_obj_asuint32(dscpobj) > 63) {
665 cfg_obj_log(dscpobj, named_g_lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
666 "dscp value '%u' is out of range",
667 cfg_obj_asuint32(dscpobj));
668 result = ISC_R_RANGE;
669 goto cleanup;
670 }
671 dscp = (isc_dscp_t)cfg_obj_asuint32(dscpobj);
672 }
673
674 result = ISC_R_NOMEMORY;
675
676 element = cfg_list_first(addrlist);
677 resume:
678 for ( ;
679 element != NULL;
680 element = cfg_list_next(element))
681 {
682 const cfg_obj_t *addr;
683 const cfg_obj_t *key;
684 const char *keystr;
685 isc_buffer_t b;
686
687 addr = cfg_tuple_get(cfg_listelt_value(element),
688 "masterselement");
689 key = cfg_tuple_get(cfg_listelt_value(element), "key");
690
691 if (!cfg_obj_issockaddr(addr)) {
692 const char *listname = cfg_obj_asstring(addr);
693 isc_result_t tresult;
694
695 /* Grow lists? */
696 if (listcount == l) {
697 void * tmp;
698 uint32_t newlen = listcount + 16;
699 size_t newsize, oldsize;
700
701 newsize = newlen * sizeof(*lists);
702 oldsize = listcount * sizeof(*lists);
703 tmp = isc_mem_get(mctx, newsize);
704 if (tmp == NULL)
705 goto cleanup;
706 if (listcount != 0) {
707 memmove(tmp, lists, oldsize);
708 isc_mem_put(mctx, lists, oldsize);
709 }
710 lists = tmp;
711 listcount = newlen;
712 }
713 /* Seen? */
714 for (j = 0; j < l; j++)
715 if (strcasecmp(lists[j].name, listname) == 0)
716 break;
717 if (j < l)
718 continue;
719 tresult = named_config_getmastersdef(config, listname,
720 &list);
721 if (tresult == ISC_R_NOTFOUND) {
722 cfg_obj_log(addr, named_g_lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
723 "masters \"%s\" not found", listname);
724
725 result = tresult;
726 goto cleanup;
727 }
728 if (tresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
729 goto cleanup;
730 lists[l++].name = listname;
731 /* Grow stack? */
732 if (stackcount == pushed) {
733 void * tmp;
734 uint32_t newlen = stackcount + 16;
735 size_t newsize, oldsize;
736
737 newsize = newlen * sizeof(*stack);
738 oldsize = stackcount * sizeof(*stack);
739 tmp = isc_mem_get(mctx, newsize);
740 if (tmp == NULL)
741 goto cleanup;
742 if (stackcount != 0) {
743 memmove(tmp, stack, oldsize);
744 isc_mem_put(mctx, stack, oldsize);
745 }
746 stack = tmp;
747 stackcount = newlen;
748 }
749 /*
750 * We want to resume processing this list on the
751 * next element.
752 */
753 stack[pushed].element = cfg_list_next(element);
754 stack[pushed].port = port;
755 stack[pushed].dscp = dscp;
756 pushed++;
757 goto newlist;
758 }
759
760 if (i == addrcount) {
761 void * tmp;
762 uint32_t newlen = addrcount + 16;
763 size_t newsize, oldsize;
764
765 newsize = newlen * sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t);
766 oldsize = addrcount * sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t);
767 tmp = isc_mem_get(mctx, newsize);
768 if (tmp == NULL)
769 goto cleanup;
770 if (addrcount != 0) {
771 memmove(tmp, addrs, oldsize);
772 isc_mem_put(mctx, addrs, oldsize);
773 }
774 addrs = tmp;
775 addrcount = newlen;
776
777 newsize = newlen * sizeof(isc_dscp_t);
778 oldsize = dscpcount * sizeof(isc_dscp_t);
779 tmp = isc_mem_get(mctx, newsize);
780 if (tmp == NULL)
781 goto cleanup;
782 if (dscpcount != 0) {
783 memmove(tmp, dscps, oldsize);
784 isc_mem_put(mctx, dscps, oldsize);
785 }
786 dscps = tmp;
787 dscpcount = newlen;
788
789 newsize = newlen * sizeof(dns_name_t *);
790 oldsize = keycount * sizeof(dns_name_t *);
791 tmp = isc_mem_get(mctx, newsize);
792 if (tmp == NULL)
793 goto cleanup;
794 if (keycount != 0) {
795 memmove(tmp, keys, oldsize);
796 isc_mem_put(mctx, keys, oldsize);
797 }
798 keys = tmp;
799 keycount = newlen;
800 }
801
802 addrs[i] = *cfg_obj_assockaddr(addr);
803 if (isc_sockaddr_getport(&addrs[i]) == 0)
804 isc_sockaddr_setport(&addrs[i], port);
805 dscps[i] = cfg_obj_getdscp(addr);
806 if (dscps[i] == -1)
807 dscps[i] = dscp;
808 keys[i] = NULL;
809 i++; /* Increment here so that cleanup on error works. */
810 if (!cfg_obj_isstring(key))
811 continue;
812 keys[i - 1] = isc_mem_get(mctx, sizeof(dns_name_t));
813 if (keys[i - 1] == NULL)
814 goto cleanup;
815 dns_name_init(keys[i - 1], NULL);
816
817 keystr = cfg_obj_asstring(key);
818 isc_buffer_constinit(&b, keystr, strlen(keystr));
819 isc_buffer_add(&b, strlen(keystr));
820 dns_fixedname_init(&fname);
821 result = dns_name_fromtext(dns_fixedname_name(&fname), &b,
822 dns_rootname, 0, NULL);
823 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
824 goto cleanup;
825 result = dns_name_dup(dns_fixedname_name(&fname), mctx,
826 keys[i - 1]);
827 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
828 goto cleanup;
829 }
830 if (pushed != 0) {
831 pushed--;
832 element = stack[pushed].element;
833 port = stack[pushed].port;
834 dscp = stack[pushed].dscp;
835 goto resume;
836 }
837 if (i < addrcount) {
838 void * tmp;
839 size_t newsize, oldsize;
840
841 newsize = i * sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t);
842 oldsize = addrcount * sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t);
843 if (i != 0) {
844 tmp = isc_mem_get(mctx, newsize);
845 if (tmp == NULL)
846 goto cleanup;
847 memmove(tmp, addrs, newsize);
848 } else
849 tmp = NULL;
850 isc_mem_put(mctx, addrs, oldsize);
851 addrs = tmp;
852 addrcount = i;
853
854 newsize = i * sizeof(isc_dscp_t);
855 oldsize = dscpcount * sizeof(isc_dscp_t);
856 if (i != 0) {
857 tmp = isc_mem_get(mctx, newsize);
858 if (tmp == NULL)
859 goto cleanup;
860 memmove(tmp, dscps, newsize);
861 } else
862 tmp = NULL;
863 isc_mem_put(mctx, dscps, oldsize);
864 dscps = tmp;
865 dscpcount = i;
866
867 newsize = i * sizeof(dns_name_t *);
868 oldsize = keycount * sizeof(dns_name_t *);
869 if (i != 0) {
870 tmp = isc_mem_get(mctx, newsize);
871 if (tmp == NULL)
872 goto cleanup;
873 memmove(tmp, keys, newsize);
874 } else
875 tmp = NULL;
876 isc_mem_put(mctx, keys, oldsize);
877 keys = tmp;
878 keycount = i;
879 }
880
881 if (lists != NULL)
882 isc_mem_put(mctx, lists, listcount * sizeof(*lists));
883 if (stack != NULL)
884 isc_mem_put(mctx, stack, stackcount * sizeof(*stack));
885
886 INSIST(keycount == addrcount);
887
888 ipkl->addrs = addrs;
889 ipkl->dscps = dscps;
890 ipkl->keys = keys;
891 ipkl->count = addrcount;
892 ipkl->allocated = addrcount;
893
894 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
895
896 cleanup:
897 if (addrs != NULL)
898 isc_mem_put(mctx, addrs, addrcount * sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t));
899 if (dscps != NULL)
900 isc_mem_put(mctx, dscps, dscpcount * sizeof(isc_dscp_t));
901 if (keys != NULL) {
902 for (j = 0; j < i; j++) {
903 if (keys[j] == NULL)
904 continue;
905 if (dns_name_dynamic(keys[j]))
906 dns_name_free(keys[j], mctx);
907 isc_mem_put(mctx, keys[j], sizeof(dns_name_t));
908 }
909 isc_mem_put(mctx, keys, keycount * sizeof(dns_name_t *));
910 }
911 if (lists != NULL)
912 isc_mem_put(mctx, lists, listcount * sizeof(*lists));
913 if (stack != NULL)
914 isc_mem_put(mctx, stack, stackcount * sizeof(*stack));
915 return (result);
916}
917
918isc_result_t
919named_config_getport(const cfg_obj_t *config, in_port_t *portp) {
920 const cfg_obj_t *maps[3];
921 const cfg_obj_t *options = NULL;
922 const cfg_obj_t *portobj = NULL;
923 isc_result_t result;
924 int i;
925
926 (void)cfg_map_get(config, "options", &options);
927 i = 0;
928 if (options != NULL)
929 maps[i++] = options;
930 maps[i++] = named_g_defaults;
931 maps[i] = NULL;
932
933 result = named_config_get(maps, "port", &portobj);
934 INSIST(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
935 if (cfg_obj_asuint32(portobj) >= UINT16_MAX) {
936 cfg_obj_log(portobj, named_g_lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
937 "port '%u' out of range",
938 cfg_obj_asuint32(portobj));
939 return (ISC_R_RANGE);
940 }
941 *portp = (in_port_t)cfg_obj_asuint32(portobj);
942 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
943}
944
945isc_result_t
946named_config_getdscp(const cfg_obj_t *config, isc_dscp_t *dscpp) {
947 const cfg_obj_t *options = NULL;
948 const cfg_obj_t *dscpobj = NULL;
949 isc_result_t result;
950
951 (void)cfg_map_get(config, "options", &options);
952 if (options == NULL)
953 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
954
955 result = cfg_map_get(options, "dscp", &dscpobj);
956 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS || dscpobj == NULL) {
957 *dscpp = -1;
958 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
959 }
960 if (cfg_obj_asuint32(dscpobj) >= 64) {
961 cfg_obj_log(dscpobj, named_g_lctx, ISC_LOG_ERROR,
962 "dscp '%u' out of range",
963 cfg_obj_asuint32(dscpobj));
964 return (ISC_R_RANGE);
965 }
966 *dscpp = (isc_dscp_t)cfg_obj_asuint32(dscpobj);
967 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
968}
969
970struct keyalgorithms {
971 const char *str;
972 enum { hmacnone, hmacmd5, hmacsha1, hmacsha224,
973 hmacsha256, hmacsha384, hmacsha512 } hmac;
974 unsigned int type;
975 uint16_t size;
976} algorithms[] = {
977 { "hmac-md5", hmacmd5, DST_ALG_HMACMD5, 128 },
978 { "hmac-md5.sig-alg.reg.int", hmacmd5, DST_ALG_HMACMD5, 0 },
979 { "hmac-md5.sig-alg.reg.int.", hmacmd5, DST_ALG_HMACMD5, 0 },
980 { "hmac-sha1", hmacsha1, DST_ALG_HMACSHA1, 160 },
981 { "hmac-sha224", hmacsha224, DST_ALG_HMACSHA224, 224 },
982 { "hmac-sha256", hmacsha256, DST_ALG_HMACSHA256, 256 },
983 { "hmac-sha384", hmacsha384, DST_ALG_HMACSHA384, 384 },
984 { "hmac-sha512", hmacsha512, DST_ALG_HMACSHA512, 512 },
985 { NULL, hmacnone, DST_ALG_UNKNOWN, 0 }
986};
987
988isc_result_t
989named_config_getkeyalgorithm(const char *str, const dns_name_t **name,
990 uint16_t *digestbits)
991{
992 return (named_config_getkeyalgorithm2(str, name, NULL, digestbits));
993}
994
995isc_result_t
996named_config_getkeyalgorithm2(const char *str, const dns_name_t **name,
997 unsigned int *typep, uint16_t *digestbits)
998{
999 int i;
1000 size_t len = 0;
1001 uint16_t bits;
1002 isc_result_t result;
1003
1004 for (i = 0; algorithms[i].str != NULL; i++) {
1005 len = strlen(algorithms[i].str);
1006 if (strncasecmp(algorithms[i].str, str, len) == 0 &&
1007 (str[len] == '\0' ||
1008 (algorithms[i].size != 0 && str[len] == '-')))
1009 break;
1010 }
1011 if (algorithms[i].str == NULL)
1012 return (ISC_R_NOTFOUND);
1013 if (str[len] == '-') {
1014 result = isc_parse_uint16(&bits, str + len + 1, 10);
1015 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
1016 return (result);
1017 if (bits > algorithms[i].size)
1018 return (ISC_R_RANGE);
1019 } else if (algorithms[i].size == 0)
1020 bits = 128;
1021 else
1022 bits = algorithms[i].size;
1023
1024 if (name != NULL) {
1025 switch (algorithms[i].hmac) {
1026 case hmacmd5: *name = dns_tsig_hmacmd5_name; break;
1027 case hmacsha1: *name = dns_tsig_hmacsha1_name; break;
1028 case hmacsha224: *name = dns_tsig_hmacsha224_name; break;
1029 case hmacsha256: *name = dns_tsig_hmacsha256_name; break;
1030 case hmacsha384: *name = dns_tsig_hmacsha384_name; break;
1031 case hmacsha512: *name = dns_tsig_hmacsha512_name; break;
1032 default:
1033 INSIST(0);
1034 ISC_UNREACHABLE();
1035 }
1036 }
1037 if (typep != NULL)
1038 *typep = algorithms[i].type;
1039 if (digestbits != NULL)
1040 *digestbits = bits;
1041 return (ISC_R_SUCCESS);
1042}
